  <Placemark>
   <name>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued October 25 at 3:25PM CDT until October 25 at 4:15PM CDT by NWS Fort Worth TX</name>
   <styleUrl>#sev_severe</styleUrl>
   <Style>
    <BalloonStyle />
   </Style>
   <Snippet>At 325 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Evant, or 20
miles south of Hamilton, moving east at 45 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and half dollar size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage to
roofs, siding, and trees.

This severe storm will be near...
Gatesville around 345 PM CDT.
Fort Gates around 355 PM CDT.

Other locations impacted by this severe thunderstorm include Pancake,
South Mountain, Purmela, Whiteway, Aleman, Arnett, Levita, Pearl,
South Purmela, and Bee House.</Snippet>
