  <Placemark>
   <name>Flood Advisory issued October 25 at 2:57PM CDT until October 25 at 6:00PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</name>
   <styleUrl>#sev_minor</styleUrl>
   <Style>
    <BalloonStyle />
   </Style>
   <Snippet>* WHAT...Small stream flooding caused by excessive rainfall is
expected.

* WHERE...A portion of west central Texas, including the following
county, San Saba.

* WHEN...Until 600 PM CDT.

* IMPACTS...Minor flooding in low-lying and poor drainage areas.
Dangerous flows over low-water crossings. Overflowing poor
drainage areas.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...
- At 257 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated heavy rain due to
thunderstorms. This will cause small stream flooding. Between
1 and 2 inches of rain have fallen.
- Additional rainfall amounts of 1 to 2 inches are expected
over the area. This additional rain will result in minor
flooding.
- Some locations that will experience flooding include...
San Saba, Richland Springs, Algerita, Sloan, Skeeterville,
Hall, Spring Creek, Harkeyville and Locker.
- This includes the following Low Water Crossings...
FM 1030 crossing Wallace Creek, CR 340 crossing San Saba
River, CR 340 crossing Dry Creek, CR 208 crossing San Saba
River, crossings along County Road 246 and crossings along
County Road 244.
- http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood</Snippet>
