  <Placemark>
   <name>Special Marine Warning issued October 25 at 2:56PM CDT until October 25 at 4:00PM CDT by NWS New Orleans LA</name>
   <styleUrl>#sev_severe</styleUrl>
   <Style>
    <BalloonStyle />
   </Style>
   <Snippet>SMWLIX

The National Weather Service in New Orleans has issued a

* Special Marine Warning for...
Coastal Waters from Port Fourchon LA to Lower Atchafalaya River LA
out 20 nm...
Coastal waters from Port Fourchon Louisiana to Lower Atchafalaya
River LA from 20 to 60 NM...

* Until 400 PM CDT.

* At 256 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm capable of producing
waterspouts was located 9 nm southwest of Caillou Bay, moving
northeast at 10 knots.

HAZARD...Waterspouts, wind gusts 34 knots or greater, and small
hail.

SOURCE...Radar.

IMPACT...Waterspouts can quickly form and capsize boats...damage
vessels and oil rigs...and create suddenly higher waves.
Small craft could be damaged in briefly higher winds and
suddenly higher waves.

* Locations impacted include...
Isle Derniers and Caillou Bay.</Snippet>
