   <name>Gale Warning issued October 25 at 2:08AM PDT until October 25 at 5:00PM PDT by NWS Medford OR</name>
   <styleUrl>#sev_moderate</styleUrl>
   <Style>
    <BalloonStyle />
   </Style>
   <Snippet>* WHAT...For the Small Craft Advisory, south winds 15 to 25 kt
with gusts up to 30 kt and seas 14 to 16 ft at 15 seconds. For
the Gale Warning, southwest winds 25 to 35 kt with gusts up to
45 kt and seas 20 to 25 ft at 15 seconds expected. For the
Hazardous Seas Warning, very steep and hazardous seas 20 to 25
ft at 14 seconds expected.

* WHERE...All the waters between Florence and Pt. St. George.

* WHEN...For the Small Craft Advisory, until 5 AM PDT Saturday.
For the Gale Warning, from 5 AM to 5 PM PDT Saturday. For the
Hazardous Seas Warning, from 5 PM Saturday to 5 AM PDT Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds and very steep seas could capsize or
damage vessels. Low visibility conditions are expected.

* View the hazard area in detail at https://go.usa.gov/x6hks</Snippet>
